</code></pre><!----></div></div></div><!----><!----><!----></code-block><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></response-element><p data-path-to-node="15">Commit changes (twice).</p><hr data-path-to-node="16"><h3 data-path-to-node="17">Step 3: Check your link on Vercel</h3><p data-path-to-node="18">Now that you have committed these last files, you are finished with GitHub.</p><p data-path-to-node="19">Go to your <b data-path-to-node="19" data-index-in-node="11">Vercel dashboard</b>, open your project, and look at the <b data-path-to-node="19" data-index-in-node="64">Deployments</b> tab. You will see that it has automatically started to rebuild. When it is finished, you will have your official <code data-path-to-node="19" data-index-in-node="189">.vercel.app</code> link. Drop it right into your Instagram bio!</p></div></message-content><!----></div></structured-content-container><!----><!----><!----><div _ngcontent-ng-c3655342764="" class="response-footer contains-extensions-response has-thoughts gap complete"><!----><!----><!----><sources-list _ngcontent-ng-c3655342764="" class="sources-list ng-star-inserted"><overview-carousel _nghost-ng-c2730877997="" class="ng-star-inserted"><div _ngcontent-ng-c2730877997="" jslog="268370;track:generic_click,impression"><!----><!----><sources-sidebar-button _ngcontent-ng-c2730877997="" _nghost-ng-c4229933914="" class="ng-star-inserted"><!----></sources-sidebar-button><!----><!----><!----><!----></div></overview-carousel><!----></sources-list><!----><!----><!----><!-